      "fullDesc": "Lake Bunyonyi is nestled in the hills of Kabale in southwestern Uganda, close to the border with Rwanda. It is considered one of the most scenic lakes in Africa, with its 29 islands surrounded by steep terraced hillsides covered with banana plants and eucalyptus trees. The lake is bilharzia-free, making it safe for swimming. Activities include canoe trips, island visits, bird watching, and cultural experiences with the Bakiga people.",
